I"V<p>Just like a physical address indicates a certain location in the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/craving-for-grounding-spawns-cartesian-anxiety">real world</a>, and how a digital address indicates the IP location in the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/digital-is-pejorative">digital realm</a>, so does a concept handle point to a certain location in <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/concept-learning-is-few-shot-scaffolding-supported-by-working-memory">conceptual space</a>. In this view, concept handles are pointers to a certain <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/physical-and-conceptual-spaces-are-coded-in-the-same-region">location in conceptual space</a>, which abstract away from <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/explicit-position-cues-describe-conceptual-structure">explicit cues</a>.</p>
